# CSS Padding

Padding creates space inside an element.

## Example

```css
div {
    padding: 20px;
}
```

## Individual Sides

```css
div {
    padding-top: 10px;
    padding-right: 15px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    padding-left: 15px;
}
```

## Button Example

```css
button {
    padding: 12px 24px;
}
```

## Real-World Example

Padding makes buttons easier to click.

## Summary

Padding improves content spacing inside elements.
